#. <section class="sutta" id="sn1.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Nandanavagga"
msgstr "2. The Garden of Delight"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Nandanasutta"
msgstr "11. The Garden of Delight"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.11:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn1.11:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn1.11:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn1.11:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn1.11:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn1.11:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: paricārayamānā → paricāriyamānā (s1-3, km, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn1.11:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, aññatarā tāvatiṃsakāyikā devatā nandane vane "
"accharāsaṅghaparivutā dibbehi pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā "
"paricārayamānā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, a certain deity of the company of the Thirty-"
"Three was amusing themselves in the Garden of Delight, escorted by a band of "
"nymphs, and supplied and provided with the five kinds of heavenly sensual "
"stimulation. On that occasion they recited this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.11:3.1"
msgid "‘Na te sukhaṃ pajānanti,"
msgstr "‘They don’t know pleasure"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.11:3.2"
msgid "ye na passanti nandanaṃ;"
msgstr "who don’t see the Garden of Delight!"

# BB curiously has “male god” for naradeva, citing the comm. But naradeva is a fairly common term, and it always has a sense of “lord, regal one, exalted one”, etc., never of gender.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.11:3.3"
msgid "Āvāsaṃ naradevānaṃ,"
msgstr "It’s the abode of lordly gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.11:3.4"
msgid "tidasānaṃ yasassinan’ti."
msgstr "the glorious host of Thirty!’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.11:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhikkhave, aññatarā devatā taṃ devataṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi:"
msgstr "When they had spoken, another deity replied with this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn1.11:5.1"
msgid "‘Na tvaṃ bāle pajānāsi,"
msgstr "‘Fool, don’t you understand"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.11:5.2"
msgid "yathā arahataṃ vaco;"
msgstr "the saying of the perfected ones:"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sabbasaṅkhārā → sabbe saṅkhārā (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn1.11:5.3"
msgid "Aniccā sabbasaṅkhārā,"
msgstr "All conditions are impermanent,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.11:5.4"
msgid "uppādavayadhammino;"
msgstr "their nature is to rise and fall;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.11:5.5"
msgid "Uppajjitvā nirujjhanti,"
msgstr "having arisen, they cease;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn1.11:5.6"
msgid "tesaṃ vūpasamo sukho’”ti."
msgstr "their stilling is true bliss.’”"
